A man-in-the-middle attack happens when someone secretly intercepts and possibly alters the communication between two people without their knowledge. Imagine sending a message, but an unseen person reads or changes it before it reaches the other side. This puts privacy and data at risk. Using tools that encrypt messages directly between users, without relying on middle servers, helps stop these attacks. To learn more, look up terms like “MITM attack,” “end-to-end encryption,” and “secure communication.”